title: Meet Team NutriBullet- Raine
description:
We're gearing up for the LA Marathon and we'd like to introduce some fabulous members of our NutriBullet running team! Meet Raine, a schoolteacher and avid runner.  
Music from http://incompetech.com

For more information, please visit: http://po.st/TeamNutriBullet

Follow us on Social Media @TeamNutriBullet:
Facebook: http://www.Facebook.com/TeamNutriBullet
Twitter: http://www.Twitter.com/TeamNutriBullet
Instagram: http://www.Instagram.com/TeamNutriBullet
transcripts: My name is rainy Mitchell and I teach preschool exercise and nutrition are really important to be like healthy as being you can be but I think nutrition is a priority even more so than exercise because there's immediate results I used to be such a fan of oatmeal before my run I would only be able to eat oatmeal and a banana or something of that nature we're gonna get some kale and my favorite fruit blueberries my super food we flaxseed and of course I'll need some almond milk and I like just a little bit on the better at night, so what do you call I don't have a name for it I don't call it an evening almond delight. I feel like the nutribullet has really helped me my recovery with just really great wholesome foods I haven't used something so much like to its fullest potential like you know like you get clothing and you know you use it and you throw it away after a while you know but this is like it's a solid foundation like you like people use it all the time I don't know anybody who has their nutribullet and doesn't use it. All of my friends are really like either have gotten one or like super jealous so I think it's essential for not only just runners but almost any athlete.
